":5,"description":"Raw model output is captured to a diagnostic artifact before any JSON parsing or extraction logic runs.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"MOCK-MISS: The failure is a pipeline ordering bug at the boundary between the model call, the capture step, and the parser. If each step is tested in isolation, the ordering constraint is never verified. REAL-INFRA: Writing a local file artifact is in-process filesystem I/O; a real filesystem path (temp dir) is sufficient and no subprocess or real network call is needed. LLM-DEP: A stub model that returns a fixed string is sufficient — the behavior concerns capture-before-parse ordering, not model output quality. MULTI-STEP: None. REJECTION-GATE: System rejected because real HTTP/OS primitives are not required; a real local temp file exercises the artifact capture path faithfully.","test_description":"Wire together the model stub (returns a fixed raw string), the output capture module (writes to a temp file), and the JSON parser. Inject a deliberate JSON parse failure for the stub output. Assert that the diagnostic artifact file exists and contains the raw string even after the parse failure — proving capture occurred before parsing was attempted. Also assert the artifact is absent when the pipeline is invoked without enabling capture, to verify the guard is deliberate.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.1,"Integration":0.76,"System":0.1,"Agentic":0.04,"Workflow":0}},{"behavior_id":6,"description":"Assertions verify structured behavior (for example field placement or schema shape), not mere keyword presence that could come from prompt echoing.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"MOCK-MISS: The failure is at the boundary between the test assertion logic and the model output fixture: an assertion that only checks keyword presence would pass even on a response that merely echoes the prompt. Verifying this requires running the assertion code against a crafted output that satisfies keyword presence but violates schema structure, and confirming the assertion fires. A single-function unit test on the assertion predicate in isolation would not capture how it interacts with real output shapes. REAL-INFRA: No real network or LLM needed; a synthetic fixed output is sufficient. LLM-DEP: None — correctness is determined by the assertion predicate logic, not by model output variability. REJECTION-GATE: Agentic rejected because no real LLM call is needed; the synthetic output fully controls the test condition.","test_description":"Construct two synthetic model output fixtures: (A) a response that contains the expected keywords but places them in the wrong schema field or wrong nesting level, and (B) a correctly structured response. Run the test suite's assertion logic against both. Assert that (A) fails assertions (proving structural checking) and (B) passes (proving the assertions are not over-restrictive). A purely keyword-based assertion would incorrectly pass for (A), making this the disqualifying oracle.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.18,"Integration":0.68,"System":0.04,"Agentic":0.09,"Workflow":0.01}}]},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":3,"cache_creation_input_tokens":9841,"cache_read_input_tokens":3199,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":9841},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"896d33e9-cee9-4ad8-bfd1-2831e288db12","uuid":"5fe7e755-85da-4abf-b5b4-36584914f57a"}
